  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "*Description*:\r\nCurrently [Envoy Mobile](https://github.com/lyft/envoy-mobile) uses (effectively) a single dynamic forward proxy cluster for all of its traffic. This results in dramatically simpler ergonomics for users of the library. However, it reduces the granularity of metrics available because all traffic is going through the same cluster.\r\n\r\nThis is a perfect use case for [Virtual Clusters](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/api-v2/api/v2/route/route_components.proto#envoy-api-msg-route-virtualcluster), specially since commonly users are only interested in granular traffic for a small percentage of requests. Hence that percentage can be segmented as desired using virtual clusters.\r\n\r\nCurrently virtual clusters only expose:\r\n```\r\nupstream_rq_<*xx> - Counter - Aggregate HTTP response codes (e.g., 2xx, 3xx, etc.)\r\nupstream_rq_<*> - Counter - Specific HTTP response codes (e.g., 201, 302, etc.)\r\nupstream_rq_time - Histogram - Request time milliseconds\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis ticket tracks exposing a couple more metrics of interest:\r\n```\r\nupstream_rq_timeout - Counter - Total requests that timed out waiting for a response\r\nupstream_rq_per_try_timeout - Counter - Total requests that hit the per try timeout\r\nupstream_rq_retry - Counter - Total request retries\r\nupstream_rq_retry_success - Counter - Total request retry successes\r\nupstream_rq_total - Counter - Total request\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote: relatedly if a user is interested in per vhost, per route stats _for all_ vhosts, routes there is an open issue https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/3351",
